1
00:00:22,899 --> 00:00:27,686
Tap the chest and hear the hollow ring,

2
00:00:27,686 --> 00:00:32,633
The body keeping count of everything.

3
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:37,180
I stand before the court of accounts

4
00:00:37,180 --> 00:00:40,581
And lay the story out, to all what it amounts

5
00:00:40,930 --> 00:00:44,761
Weigh it good, weigh it clear,

6
00:00:44,761 --> 00:00:48,112
What cracks the heart, but it's own fear.

7
00:00:48,112 --> 00:00:50,744
Not sin nor virtue, not a judge nor saint.

8
00:00:50,744 --> 00:00:53,616
take the messure of things, small and quaint

9
00:00:53,616 --> 00:00:58,963
featherlight heart, want only its part.

10
00:00:58,963 --> 00:01:02,362
born of the ledger from where shall it start.

11
00:01:02,713 --> 00:01:20,745
Words lodged on the bottom, river stone,

12
00:01:20,745 --> 00:01:25,451
Form of breath and marrow grown in the bone.

13
00:01:25,451 --> 00:01:31,516
Could not tell you why, these choices I made.

14
00:01:31,516 --> 00:01:36,911
Was it due, or to the heart it weighed.

15
00:01:37,260 --> 00:01:39,813
A needle settles, the pivot stills,

16
00:01:39,813 --> 00:01:42,527
Done the accounting of my honest ills.

17
00:01:42,527 --> 00:01:44,201
Cannot claim, this was not I.

18
00:01:44,201 --> 00:01:58,134
Clear as day, bright blue sky.

19
00:01:58,483 --> 00:02:00,798
I close the book, now ledger thin,

20
00:02:00,798 --> 00:02:03,750
This time around, what did I win?

21
00:02:03,750 --> 00:02:06,144
Set, ready, ready to go.

22
00:02:06,144 --> 00:02:08,616
Would do this again,

23
00:02:08,616 --> 00:02:09,703
if you must know.

24
00:02:10,052 --> 00:02:16,995
Close up the shop,

25
00:02:16,995 --> 00:02:19,627
only for today.

26
00:02:19,627 --> 00:02:21,782
Back home, on my pillow

27
00:02:21,782 --> 00:02:24,574
this weary head I lay.
